2 and 1/2 stars.  Since there is no half in the ratings, so it got 3. Average American-Chinese restaurant, served up some familiar dishes that people in America is familiar with.  It generally has no style of any region in China.  This hodge podge approach would satisfy the mass, but bothers the heck out of the "foodie" whom would look for some style of cooking to pin on. We stay away from its big fat egg rolls, and its greasy fried rice.  Instead, we asked for basil chicken, garlic pepper shrimps, and stir fried bok choy.  We ate them over steamed rice. The bok choy was the best.  Hot wok did wonder for the vegetable.  Basil chicken and garlic pepper shrimps are passable.  A tad salty, but did not taste so bad after all. Service was good.  Food came out promptly.  We did not have to ask for anything.

I was recommended this place by a friend and i decided to try it out. I ordered food with the app for my friends and I and we had waited past the “expected” delivery time. I understand that this is only an estimate and with crazy weather, people may be running late. I called to ask about my order when it was 30 minutes late. The person over the phone told me that the delivery driver would be on his way shortly. After about 55 minutes I called again to ask where the food was again, and the person over the phone was clearly upset, stating that they had called me ten times and that I didn't answer the phone calls. I never received a phone call. The phone was then passed off to a woman, who explained to me the situation. I asked her to re-read to me the phone number they had given the driver, because I was checking the app and looking at my phone number and it was correct. She read the phone number, and it was incorrect. She then said “someone must’ve put it in wrong” without apologizing for the mess that wasn’t even my fault anymore. To add on to this stress even more, the delivery driver was unbelievably rude. He was upset that I “hadn’t” answered his phone calls, and when i tried to explain to him that someone gave him the wrong number he scoffed at me. He was also upset that I did not give him a cash tip. I had already tipped on the app but he was very adamant that he receive a cash one as well because he had to come back with the food a second time. Overall, this was such an upsetting experience. The way the situation was handled and the way I was spoken to, yelled and belittled by the delivery driver was just not worth the food.
